3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Hyperliquid calculates FIL/USDT funding rates every hour using a time-weighted premium/discount to spot prices across multiple exchanges. The on-chain order book enables transparent rate discovery without order flow manipulation common on centralized venues. Funding payments occur automatically through smart contracts, with rates typically ranging from -0.1% to +0.3% annually depending on market sentiment toward decentralized storage adoption."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","FIL","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"FIL presents compelling funding arbitrage potential due to its correlation with enterprise storage adoption cycles and Web3 infrastructure narratives. The token's moderate volatility and consistent trading volume create stable funding rate environments ideal for carry strategies, while Hyperliquid's 1-hour intervals provide more frequent rebalancing opportunities compared to 8-hour standard intervals."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"FIL/USDT funding rates on Hyperliquid have historically shown positive bias during storage upgrade announcements and negative rates during broader crypto downturns. The 1-hour funding mechanism creates smoother rate transitions compared to 8-hour cycles, with typical daily ranges of 0.02% to 0.08%. Storage milestone events like Filecoin Plus program expansions often drive temporary funding spikes above 0.15% as sentiment shifts toward infrastructure tokens."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Cross-Exchange Arbitrage Opportunities"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Hyperliquid's transparent on-chain rate calculation often leads to temporary divergences from centralized exchanges like Binance and OKX. The 1-hour funding cycle creates 8x more rebalancing opportunities per day, allowing arbitrageurs to capture rate differences more frequently. FIL's infrastructure narrative attracts different trader demographics across venues, creating persistent basis spreads that sophisticated arbitrageurs can exploit through delta-neutral positions."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Management Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"FIL funding arbitrage on Hyperliquid requires careful attention to the platform's USDC-only settlement and potential smart contract risks inherent to on-chain derivatives. The token's correlation with broader infrastructure narratives means funding rates can shift rapidly during sector rotation events. Traders should monitor Filecoin network utilization metrics and storage provider economics, as fundamental changes in storage demand directly impact perpetual funding dynamics beyond typical technical factors."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"Why does Hyperliquid's 1-hour funding benefit FIL arbitrage strategies?","answer":"The 1-hour funding cycle allows more precise capture of FIL's volatility patterns tied to storage announcements and infrastructure news. This creates 8x more rebalancing opportunities compared to traditional 8-hour cycles, enabling better risk management during FIL's characteristic news-driven price movements."},{"question":"How do FIL storage economics affect funding rates on Hyperliquid?","answer":"FIL funding rates correlate with storage provider profitability and network capacity utilization. When storage deals increase or new enterprise clients join, FIL demand often pushes funding rates positive as traders anticipate price appreciation from fundamental storage adoption."},{"question":"What makes FIL different from other infrastructure tokens for funding arbitrage?","answer":"FIL has more predictable fundamental drivers through storage network metrics compared to speculative infrastructure tokens. The measurable storage deals and provider economics create clearer arbitrage signals when funding rates diverge from underlying network value accrual."},{"question":"Are there specific risks trading FIL perpetuals on a DEX versus CEX?","answer":"Hyperliquid's on-chain nature means smart contract risk and potential network congestion during high volatility. However, the transparent order book and elimination of custodial risk often provide better execution for FIL funding strategies, especially during infrastructure sector rotations when CEX funding can become extremely skewed."}]}]
